---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const effectiveDate = 'March 23, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Orbit Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy Policy for Orbit, a local-first personal CRM."
>
  <style>
    .wrap {
      width: min(calc(100% - 32px), 820px);
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .card {
      padding: 34px;
    }

    h1,
    h2 {
      line-height: 1.15;
    }

    h1 {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, 4rem);
      letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    }

    h2 {
      margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;
      font-size: 1.2rem;
    }

    p,
    li {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    ul {
      padding-left: 1.2rem;
    }

    .meta {
      margin: 12px 0 1.5rem;
      color: var(--accent-strong);
    }

    @media (max-width: 720px) {
      .card {
        padding: 24px;
      }
    }
  </style>

  <div class="wrap">
    <section class="card panel">
      <h1>Privacy Policy for Orbit</h1>
      <p class="meta">Effective date: {effectiveDate}</p>

      <p>
        Orbit is a local-first personal CRM published by Lasdw. This Privacy Policy explains how
        Orbit handles user and device data.
      </p>

      <h2>Summary</h2>
      <p>
        Orbit does not require an account. Orbit does not sell data. Orbit does not use analytics,
        advertising SDKs, or cloud sync. The information you enter into the app is stored locally
        on your device.
      </p>

      <h2>What data Orbit handles</h2>
      <p>Orbit allows you to enter and store information such as:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>names and relationship notes</li>
        <li>meeting notes and follow-up dates</li>
        <li>
          optional profile details you choose to enter, such as company, role, city, school, phone
          number, email address, and social links
        </li>
        <li>tags and other organizational metadata you create inside the app</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How data is collected</h2>
      <p>
        Orbit only handles information that you manually enter into the app. The current version of
        Orbit does not import contacts from your device and does not request contacts permission.
      </p>

      <h2>How data is used</h2>
      <p>
        Data is used only to provide the app&apos;s core functionality, including storing people,
        organizing notes, and helping you remember context for personal and professional
        relationships.
      </p>

      <h2>Data sharing and transmission</h2>
      <p>
        Orbit does not transmit, share, or sell the personal information you enter to the
        developer or to third parties. Data remains on your device unless you choose to export,
        copy, back up, or share your device data through tools outside the app.
      </p>

      <h2>Data storage, retention, and deletion</h2>
      <p>
        Data is stored locally on your device using on-device app storage. Data remains on your
        device until you edit or delete it, or until you uninstall the app or clear the app&apos;s
        data through your device settings.
      </p>

      <h2>Security</h2>
      <p>
        Orbit uses the storage and security features provided by the operating system and app
        sandbox. No method of storage is guaranteed to be perfectly secure, but Orbit is designed
        to minimize exposure by keeping your data local to your device.
      </p>

      <h2>Children</h2>
      <p>
        Orbit is not designed for children under 13. If you do not intend to distribute the app to
        children, do not include children under 13 in your Google Play target audience settings.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Any updated version should be posted
        at the same public URL used in the app store listing.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Developer: Lasdw<br />
        App: Orbit<br />
        Contact: <a href="mailto:vividh999@gmail.com">vividh999@gmail.com</a>
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
